police employees at prepaid taxi stands, or merchants in all but the most upscale businesses. count your cash before handing it over, and be insistent on receiving the correct change. agree on all fares and payments for services clearly in advance. being told that you can pay "as you like" is a sure warning sign. for "tour guides" who refuse to leave you alone, ignore them - do not give them any money. taxis and autorickshaws are unfortunately where you'll be most commonly ripped off as a foreigner - and dealing with them can be incredibly tiring. don't give more 